  "notes": [
    "RF path: RF_IN_PORT → C2 (10pF DC block) → U1 pad 2 → MMIC → U1 pad 8 → C3 (100pF DC block) → RF_OUT_PORT",
    "Bias path: VDD → L2 (39nH RF choke) → U1 pad 8 (combined RF-OUT/DC-IN)",
    "L1 (18nH) shunts RF-IN node to GND — provides DC return path and input ESD protection",
    "C1 (10nF) bypasses VDD rail to GND adjacent to L2 — keep as close as possible",
    "Pads 11 and 12 MUST FLOAT — do not connect to GND (unlike pads 1,3-7,9,10)",
    "GND paddle requires full solder coverage — 4 thermal vias in 2×2 grid at 0.9mm pitch",
    "Via size 0.6mm / drill 0.3mm — via-to-via gap 0.3mm (≥0.25mm DRC clearance)",
    "50Ω controlled impedance traces for RF path — keep RF traces short and direct",
    "No 90° bends on RF traces — all corners use 45° diagonal segments",
    "All NC pads (1,3-7,9,10) tied to GND plane for thermal and signal integrity"
